- "top-priority orders" refers to orders with a service level of 1;
- "last year" refers to the year 2020 in this context;
- "running critically low" means the stock quantity is equal to or below the reorder level.

- Service level 1 refers to the highest priority orders;
- Total revenue is calculated as the sum of the product of ordered quantity and total amount;
- High-priority orders are considered the most urgent orders.

- 'more standard service level orders' refers to service levels above 2; 
- 'overall earnings' means the sum of the total amounts of the orders; 
- 'finalized' orders are those with a status of 'completed'.
